				"anchor": "cittadella-nuova",
				"carousel_id": null,
				"body": "<p>On the eastern side of Central Pisa is the Cittadella Nuova, a large citadel fortress built in the 15th century which is located along the Arno River. Today only the shell of the medieval walls of the citadel remain, which surrounded a park and gardens. Around this citadel you’ll find many photogenic spots, and you can even walk along parts of the walls of the fortress.</p>",
